A schoolboy was critically injured when he was electrocuted at a school in Westville this afternoon, Highway Mail reports. ER24 paramedics were called to the school and lead into the classroom, where they found the boy, said ER24 s spokesperson, Russel Meiring. READ MORE: Child allegedly electrocuted by exposed municipal cable He noted the boy, who is believed to be 15 years old, had serious burns to his chest and hands and was in a critical condition. It is believed that the learners were using a transformer-like device when he was electrocuted, said Meiring. The learner was treated at the school and taken to St Augustine s Hospital. -Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.